{
  "answer": "**The matlaʿ (opening couplet, or maṭlaʿ) of Mīrzā Ghālib's famous ghazal is:**\n\n> دلِ ناداں تجھے ہوا کیا ہے  \n> آخر اس درد کی دوا کیا ہے<sup>[1]</sup>\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 36 (\"Dil-e-naadaan tujhe hua kya hai\"), [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/36-dil-e-naadaan-tujhe-hua-kya-hai/original/#p-7ae9d0).\n\n**Transliteration:**  \nDil-e-nādān tujhe huā kyā hai  \nĀkhir is dard kī dawā kyā hai.[^2]\n\n**Translation:**  \nMy foolish heart, what's led you to this sway?  \nFor this deep pain, what is the healing way? Pray, what is it?[^3]\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 36, transliteration variant.[^4]  \n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 36, translation variant.[^5]  \n[^4]: `/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/36-dil-e-naadaan-tujhe-hua-kya-hai/transliteration/#p-2b6870` (first paragraph).  \n[^5]: `/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/36-dil-e-naadaan-tujhe-hua-kya-hai/translation/#p-414b38` (first paragraph).",
